Introduction to AWS CloudWatch

Explain CloudWatch Events to a non-technical friend.
Cloudwatch is essentially a dashboard where the overall health, metrics and status of your various AWS services
are visible.  Cloudwatch logs events and has all your settings front and center.

What do CloudWatch Logs helps us achieve?
Troubleshooting, quesrying and filtering and compliance all in one centralized location.

What capabilities does CloudWatch Anomaly detection have?
It helps monitor unusual behavior in metrics through pattern recognition (established through a baseline), checking historical usage
and connecting alerts to get the human's attention.

